The paper deals with the problem of ranking a collection of objects using pairwise comparisons, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper proposes an algorithm that can identify a ranking using a small number of pairwise comparisons, which is a topic of interest in the field of active learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information theory and signal processing, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
